snippet.textDisplay: This is cool and all, but it's just a 96L 3D NAND chip, which, as far as I can tell, Micron, SKH, and Samsung are also all producing. The only potentially interesting thing is that Toshiba/Kioxia does integrated controllers on their NAND chips, but I can't tell if they're doing this on their BiCS, their 3D NAND, chips; but the big three could also do this just as easily, so it's a moot point at the end of the day.
snippet.textOriginal: This is cool and all, but it's just a 96L 3D NAND chip, which, as far as I can tell, Micron, SKH, and Samsung are also all producing.
